Description: Foot and wall sherd of black-glazed pottery olpe (?); fine orange-buff clay with much mica; concave disc foot; interior reserved; exterior: glazed black, misfired reddish; reserved: lowest part of edge of foot and underside; incised inscription on underside.
Curator's comments: The clay points strongly to an East Greek, not Attic provenance.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 537)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.2081)
